    <div class="mt-16 p-6 bg-off-white rounded-xl border border-border">
      <h2 class="!text-lg mb-3">What to Look for in an AI Visibility Audit</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">Not all AI audits are created equal. When evaluating an AI visibility audit, consider: how many AI platforms does it test? Does it cover just ChatGPT, or does it include Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot, and Google AI? Does it assess the underlying signals (entity clarity, structured data, digital ecosystem) or just check whether the brand name appears in AI responses?</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">A quality AI audit should deliver actionable recommendations, not just a score. It should tell you specifically what to change, in what order, and why each change matters for AI platform visibility. The best audits are backed by original research data showing what actually works, rather than theoretical frameworks.</p>
